Chapter 1
Kolun
Itnyan time, 4:30 AM. Kolun despised getting up so early. The main reason was that he was responsible for waking up the rest of his platoon. He silently got out of bed, put on his combat gear, fastened his tactical vest, and gathered his belongings from the storage cabinet. He carefully picked up a particularly small box. He slung his rifle over his shoulder and hung his helmet on a small hook on his belt. The helmet was equipped with all the necessary gear, including a respirator, goggles, and other required items. After checking his ammunition pouch, he quietly left the barracks, his boots making a creaking sound on the muddy and icy ground.
He took out a lighter from his jacket pocket and another pocket contained a cigarette. After lighting the cigarette, he took a gentle puff, then opened the door. Over the past week, he had to use all his wits just to wake up his subordinates. He no longer used preset alarms because they didn't work half the time, and all you could hear from the speakers was a faint hissing noise.
"About to wake them up?" Kolun turned around as Lieutenant Nemic approached.
"Yes."
"What method do you plan to use this time?"
Before Kolun could reply, the door opened, and Harris, Kreis, and a few others rushed out, already dressed and ready.
"Good morning," Kreis said.
"What woke you up?" Kolun asked.
First, we really don't want to see what method you're going to use to wake everyone up today. Second, the first ones to get up can enjoy the breakfast first," a soldier named Raver replied. "You know how bad that breakfast is."
Kolun said, "You're right, Sergeant Raver." He reached out and pressed the switch. Instantly, the barracks was filled with a piercing alarm. He heard someone shouting inside, followed by a flurry of hurried footsteps.
"Oh my God, Valturi," Nemic said. "I thought they would have learned to wake up with you by now."
"My training squad did it," Kolun said, pointing at Harris, Kreis, and Raver. "But to be fair, their platoon sergeant and section leader make sure to wake up before their soldiers."
A few seconds later, the rest of the platoon came rushing out. They were all dressed and ready. Some new recruits looked groggy, while others seemed extremely irritable.
"Good morning, everyone," Kolun said cheerfully.
"To be frank, Lieutenant, why are you using that method to wake us up?" a Ranger ( corporal ) asked.
"Because those regular alarms are garbage. And Daybreak never sleeps late," Kolun said.
Take your personal items," Kolun continued. As a Lieutenant and副指挥官, he had the responsibility to assist Captain Baltin肖 in overseeing and leading the company. "We won't be coming back. Senior Sergeants and Lieutenants, give your troops and yourselves 15 minutes for final checks and bring the rations needed for today."
The members of Exodus Company quickly dispersed. They were part of the Second Group Army's Second Ranger Regiment. Before the merger, they were two separate companies, Cohort and Dagger. This was a elite unit, and Kolun felt a complex mix of emotions about being promoted to Lieutenant for many reasons.
Kolun walked side by side with Lieutenant Nemic along the brightly lit road of the base. The lights on both sides were powered by generators, mostly red to help them avoid enemy bombers. To strike them, Daybreak had begun using the "Weasels" tactic in the air and on the ground.
"A new day, a new mission for Hell Vanguard," Nemic said with a dry laugh. "Where are we being sent again?"
"Some forward base outside Iainlos. We're there to support the ground offensive." Kolun took a drag on his cigarette. He blamed Kreis for getting him addicted but thought about all the battles they'd been through over the past year, so he said nothing.
"That's terrible. The front is in dire straits," Nemic said softly. "Why not send some support to Haulan instead of here?"
"Good point, brother." Kolun flicked the butt of his cigarette into the mud. "We'll walk with the first tank platoon. Captain Baltin should be there. He usually is."
"Lieutenant Xiao is having us ride with them?" Lieutenant Nemic asked in surprise.
"Yes. To be honest, he's not as bad as I imagined. I mean, he's not great, but he's not someone I dislike either."
Kolun raised his thumb and forefinger, pressing against the throat microphone, then shifted his backpack to his back. "All units of Exodus Company, gather at the west vehicle depot after completing your mission. We will depart with the first tank platoon at 05:00."
Every few seconds, he received replies from the team leaders. When they first arrived, Harris, Kreis, and Raver were lower-ranking sergeants. Since their basic training on Earth, the four of them had become good friends. Kolun felt as if knowing them was something from long ago, even though it had only been less than two years. They were all team leaders. But since the platoon sergeant was injured and retired last week after being hit by Daybreak's sniper, Kreis had taken over leadership of the second platoon.
When they walked into the vehicle depot, Kolun and Nemic's eyes fell upon about eight Kronos main battle tanks and four Stryker armored vehicles. The crews bustled about, ensuring their war machines were in proper working order. Kolun soon spotted Captain Baltin Xiao in the crowd, speaking with the commander of the tank platoon. As they approached, Captain Xiao glanced at them and came forward, his usual cold expression showing no emotion.
"Lieutenant Nemic... Lieutenant Valturi..." he said, Kolun slowed his pace. Captain Xiao looked at Kolun's holster and then raised his head. "Should the platoon be ready by now?"
